# Release Workflow

## Mandatory command

When releasing MarkerOn, **only** use:

```bash
npm run release patch   # bug fixes (most common)
npm run release minor   # new features
npm run release major   # breaking changes
```

Optional dry run: `npm run release patch --dry-run`

Pre-check only: `npm run release:check`

## Never do manually

- Edit version in `package.json` / `Cargo.toml` / lockfiles by hand
- `git tag vX.Y.Z` + `git push origin vX.Y.Z` without the script
- Write release notes before publish (CI generates them)

## Commit format (feeds release notes)

Daily commits must follow Conventional Commits — use `npm run commit`:

| Prefix | Release section |
|--------|-----------------|
| `feat:` | ✨ New |
| `fix:` / `hotfix:` | 🛠 Fixes |
| `docs:` | 📚 Documentation |
| `ci:` / `build:` | 👷 CI |
| other | 🧹 Improvements |

## Config files (do not duplicate logic elsewhere)

- `scripts/release.mjs` — local release automation
- `.github/release.yml` — GitHub note categories
- `.github/workflows/release.yml` — CI build + note generation

Full details: `.cursor/skills/release/SKILL.md`
